.TH "HTMLLABELELEMENT.FORM" "3JS" "September 29, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLLabelElement.form \- HTMLLabelElement: form property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]form\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLLabelElement\f[R] interface returns an
\f[CR]HTMLFormElement\f[R] object that owns the \f[CR]control\f[R]
associated with this \f[CR]<label>\f[R], or \f[CR]null\f[R] if this
label is not associated with a labelable form\-associated element
(\f[CR]<button>\f[R], \f[CR]<input>\f[R], \f[CR]<output>\f[R],
\f[CR]<select>\f[R], \f[CR]<textarea>\f[R], or \c
.UR https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/custom-elements.html#form-associated-custom-element
form\-associated custom elements
.UE \c
) that is owned by a form.
.PP
Unlike form\-associated elements, the \f[CR]<label>\f[R] element does
not have a \f[CR]form\f[R] attribute.
This property does not reflect any HTML attribute, but is just a
shortcut for \f[CR]label.control.form\f[R].
.SH VALUE
An \f[CR]HTMLFormElement\f[R] or \f[CR]null\f[R].
.SH SEE ALSO
